message: Growth serum strategy: One application is almost always good, increasing value significantly (20-35). A second growth can sometimes increase value (e.g., medium+medium from 20 to 30), but often drops it (e.g., large+medium, or large+small). Never apply a third growth, it consistently drops value. Mutation catalyst strategy: One mutation after growth usually drops value to 0 or negative. However, applying a *second* mutation after the first dropped value to 0 (specifically on a super-grown medium+medium land animal combo) resulted in the highest value of 60. A third mutation also causes a drastic value drop. The optimal path I found was: combine two medium land animals, apply growth serum twice, then apply mutation catalyst twice.

Prioritize the large animal combinations for the highest scores. Good luck!
